==English==

=== Pronunciation ===
*[[w:SAMPA|SAMPA]]: /'/
*[[w:IPA|IPA]]: /'hεɳ/

=== Intransitive Verb ===

'''to hang''' ([[hung]], hung)

# To be or remain [[suspend]]ed
#: ''The lights hung from the ceiling.''
#: ''The smoke hung in the air.''
# To be [[executed]] by [[suspension]] by one's neck from a [[gallows]] or a [[tree]], attached by a [[rope]] tied into a [[noose]]
#: ''You will hang for this, my friend.''
#: ''The culprits were hung from the nearest tree.''
#(''colloquial'') To spend time with, doing nothing in particular (more often ''[[to hang out with]]'')
#: ''Are you busy, or can you hang with me?''
#(''colloquial'') To loiter ([[hang about]])
#: ''I didn't see anything, officer.  I was just hanging.''

===Transitive verb===

# To suspend.
#: ''Hang those lights from the ceiling.''
# (''chess'') To make vulnerable to capture.
#: ''If you move there, you'll hang your queen rook.''

